# Cloud Hosting — DigitalOcean

## What This Skill Covers
Provisioning and managing the DigitalOcean infrastructure that runs the trading bot 24/7. Covers Droplet setup, firewall rules, managed databases, block storage, monitoring, and deployment automation.

## Recommended Architecture
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              DigitalOcean                   │
│                                             │
│  ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐   │
│  │  Droplet    │     │  Managed DB      │   │
│  │  (Bot)      │────▶│  (PostgreSQL)    │   │
│  │  2vCPU/4GB  │     │  Trade logs      │   │
│  └─────────────┘     └──────────────────┘   │
│         │                                   │
│  ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐   │
│  │  Block      │     │  Spaces (S3)     │   │
│  │  Storage    │     │  Model backups   │   │
│  │  (Data)     │     │  Historical data │   │
│  └─────────────┘     └──────────────────┘   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Droplet Specification
```yaml
# Recommended Droplet for trading bot
name:     kalshi-bot-prod
region:   nyc3           # New York — lowest latency to Kalshi
size:     s-2vcpu-4gb    # 2 vCPU, 4GB RAM — sufficient for bot + ML
image:    ubuntu-24-04-x64
backups:  true           # Enable automated backups
monitoring: true         # Enable DO monitoring agent

# Estimated cost: ~$24/month + $5 backups = ~$29/month
```

## Initial Droplet Setup
```bash
# 1. Create non-root user
adduser botuser
usermod -aG sudo botuser
su - botuser

# 2. Configure SSH key auth only (disable password auth)
mkdir ~/.ssh && chmod 700 ~/.ssh
echo "YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY" >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys

# Edit /etc/ssh/sshd_config:
# PasswordAuthentication no
# PermitRootLogin no
sudo systemctl restart sshd

# 3. Configure UFW firewall
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing
sudo ufw allow OpenSSH
sudo ufw allow 9090  # Prometheus metrics (internal only)
sudo ufw enable

# 4. Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y fail2ban htop curl git unzip
```

## Firewall Rules (DigitalOcean Cloud Firewall)
```
# Inbound rules — minimal surface
SSH (22)     → Your IP only (not 0.0.0.0/0)
Metrics (9090) → Monitoring Droplet IP only

# Outbound rules — bot needs these
HTTPS (443)  → api.anthropic.com (if used)
HTTPS (443)  → trading-api.kalshi.com
WSS   (443)  → trading-api.kalshi.com (WebSocket)
PostgreSQL (5432) → Managed DB IP only
```

## Managed PostgreSQL Setup
```bash
# Create via DO console or doctl
doctl databases create kalshi-db \
  --engine pg \
  --version 16 \
  --size db-s-1vcpu-1gb \
  --region nyc3 \
  --num-nodes 1

# Connect from Droplet using connection string from DO console
# Store in environment variable — never hardcode

# Required tables
CREATE TABLE trades (
    id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
    strategy        VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    market          VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    direction       VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
    entry_price     DECIMAL(10,4),
    exit_price      DECIMAL(10,4),
    contracts       INTEGER,
    pnl_cents       INTEGER,
    pnl_pct         DECIMAL(8,4),
    exit_reason     VARCHAR(30),
    regime          VARCHAR(10),
    candles_held    INTEGER,
    created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE TABLE bot_state (
    key             VARCHAR(100) PRIMARY KEY,
    value           JSONB,
    updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE TABLE signal_log (
    id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
    market          VARCHAR(50),
    strategy        VARCHAR(20),
    obi_value       DECIMAL(6,4),
    roc_value       DECIMAL(8,4),
    atr_regime      VARCHAR(10),
    action          VARCHAR(20),
    skip_reason     VARCHAR(50),
    created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

## Block Storage (Persistent Data Volume)
```bash
# Create and attach a volume for candle data + model files
doctl compute volume create kalshi-data \
  --size 50GiB \
  --region nyc3 \
  --fs-type ext4

# Mount the volume
sudo mkdir -p /mnt/kalshi-data
sudo mount -o discard,defaults /dev/disk/by-id/scsi-0DO_Volume_kalshi-data /mnt/kalshi-data

# Add to /etc/fstab for persistence across reboots
echo "/dev/disk/by-id/scsi-0DO_Volume_kalshi-data /mnt/kalshi-data ext4 defaults,nofail,discard 0 2" | sudo tee -a /etc/fstab

# Directory structure
/mnt/kalshi-data/
  candles/          # Historical OHLCV data
  orderbook/        # Historical OB snapshots
  models/           # Trained ML models (versioned)
  backtest_reports/ # All backtest outputs
  logs/             # Rotated application logs
```

## Environment Variables & Secrets
```bash
# Store secrets in /etc/environment (not in code or .env files committed to git)
sudo tee -a /etc/environment << EOF
KALSHI_API_KEY_ID=your_key_id
KALSHI_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=/home/botuser/.secrets/kalshi_private.pem
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@db-host:25060/kalshi?sslmode=require
DO_SPACES_KEY=your_spaces_key
DO_SPACES_SECRET=your_spaces_secret
BOT_ENV=production
EOF

# Secure the private key
mkdir ~/.secrets && chmod 700 ~/.secrets
# Copy your RSA key here
chmod 600 ~/.secrets/kalshi_private.pem
```

## Monitoring & Alerting
```bash
# Install DO monitoring agent (do this on first setup)
curl -sSL https://repos.insights.digitalocean.com/install.sh | sudo bash

# Set up alerts in DO console:
# CPU > 80% for 5 min      → Email alert
# Memory > 85%             → Email alert
# Disk > 80%               → Email alert
# Droplet unreachable      → Email + SMS alert

# Application-level alerting via simple webhook
def send_alert(msg, level="WARNING"):
    """Send to Slack/Discord webhook for trade-critical events."""
    payload = {"text": f"[{level}] Kalshi Bot: {msg}"}
    requests.post(os.getenv("ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL"), json=payload)

# Alert on:
# - Circuit breaker triggered (daily/weekly loss limit)
# - API auth failure
# - Bot process crash / restart
# - Drawdown exceeding threshold
# - Order fill failures
```

## Deployment Process
```bash
# Simple deploy script — run from local machine
#!/bin/bash
DROPLET_IP="your.droplet.ip"
DEPLOY_USER="botuser"

# 1. Push latest code
rsync -avz --exclude='.git' --exclude='__pycache__' \
  ./kalshi-bot/ ${DEPLOY_USER}@${DROPLET_IP}:/home/botuser/kalshi-bot/

# 2. SSH in and restart
ssh ${DEPLOY_USER}@${DROPLET_IP} << 'EOF'
  cd /home/botuser/kalshi-bot
  pip install -r requirements.txt --quiet
  sudo systemctl restart kalshi-bot
  sudo systemctl status kalshi-bot
EOF
```

## Backups
```bash
# Automated database backups via DO managed DB (handled automatically)
# Additional: back up models and config to DO Spaces daily

#!/bin/bash
# /etc/cron.daily/backup-bot-data
DATE=$(date +%Y%m%d)
s3cmd sync /mnt/kalshi-data/models/ s3://kalshi-backups/models/${DATE}/
s3cmd sync /home/botuser/kalshi-bot/config/ s3://kalshi-backups/config/${DATE}/
```

