## Common Pitfalls to Avoid
- **Running as root**: Always use a non-root user for the bot process
- **Hardcoded secrets**: Never commit API keys or DB passwords — use environment variables
- **No firewall**: Lock down SSH to your IP only from day one
- **Single point of failure**: Enable Droplet backups — if it gets corrupted you need a restore point
- **Ignoring disk usage**: OB snapshots fill disk fast — set up log rotation and old data archival
- **No alerting**: You won't be watching the bot 24/7 — you need alerts for critical failures
